<item>
            <title>[LU-9173] OST label tokenizer changes from = to - after first mount</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9173</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3167&quot; title=&quot;The MDT volume label tokenizer is not consistent&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3167&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3167&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but in this case the change is between an equal sign and a dash.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue can be triggered either by attempting to mount a newly-created volume by label, or an existing volume after a writeconf.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once the volume is mounted for the first time, after an unmount, it can be remounted successfully using the dash in the label.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This behavior may be common to Lustre 2.x.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>RHEL 6.8; both our lustre filesytems began at RHEL 5 Lustre 1.8.x and were upgraded from 1.8.9 to (RHEL 6) Lustre 2.4.3.</environment>
